<p>President Trump met Japan’s newly installed prime minister Sanae Takaichi in Tokyo on Tuesday, where the two leaders signed a framework agreement designed to secure supplies of rare earths and other critical minerals and to deepen bilateral economic cooperation . Officials said the pact aims to reduce reliance on a single supplier by accelerating diversified mining and processing projects and by coordinating investments and market measures . The visit also set a diplomatic tone ahead of a planned meeting between President Trump and Chinese leader Xi Jinping later in the week .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/vP4JH-QYudVDzYOczfbTHWkN7BNnHiu7LG1vxJxdVkHyZS8s1YLEKfDeM3L4aTogTr1NwONIsd-9tP_KdibP7mRV6JUeuEEmv10gMJyNACfy' alt='Japan’s Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi (R) and US President Donald Trump attend a signing ceremony after a Japan-US summit at the Akasaka State Guest House in Tokyo on October 28, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Investment package: Japan is expected to offer an investment package tied to a broader trade understanding worth about $550 billion, including purchases and projects across shipbuilding, energy and agricultural sectors, as part of the wider deal with the United States</li><li>Implementation steps: The White House said both countries will speed up financing for selected critical-mineral projects within the next six months and consider mutually complementary stockpiling arrangements to stabilize supply</li><li>Political gestures: Takaichi told the White House she plans to recommend President Trump for the Nobel Peace Prize, a move that drew both praise and criticism in regional coverage</li><li>Regional context: The agreement comes amid recent export curbs by Beijing on some minerals and chip-making equipment and ahead of a Trump–Xi meeting which officials say could address tariffs and export controls</li></ul><blockquote>The world started to enjoy more peace. - Sanae Takaichi</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Donald Trump: Trump described Japan as an &#x27;ally at the strongest level&#x27; and pledged broad U.S. support for Tokyo during the visit. (<a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/28/trump-praises-japans-new-prime-minister-saying-us-is-an-ally-at-the-strongest-level'>Euronews</a>)</li><li>Prime Minister Sanae Takaichi: Takaichi called for closer ties with the United States and said she would nominate President Trump for the Nobel Peace Prize, linking stronger bilateral ties to regional stability. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/japan-pm-takaichi-plans-to-recommend-trump-for-nobel-peace-prize/article70210927.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>Domestic critics (Japan): Some commentators accused the prime minister of &#x27;currying favour&#x27; after her announcement to recommend Trump for the Nobel Prize, arguing it risked appearing overly flattering. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3330597/japans-pm-criticised-curry-favour-trump-over-nobel-peace-prize-plan'>SCMP</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.ft.com/content/84e962b4-c8b1-43b6-9fc1-c040808fd703'>Trump and Takaichi promise ‘golden age’ for US-Japan alliance</a> - ft.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/donald-trump-asia-japan-visit-sanae-takaichi-updates-october-28-2025/article70210936.ece'>Trump, Takaichi agree on rare earth, critical minerals supply</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951751/us-japan-leaders-ink-rare-earths-deal-ahead-of-trump-xi-meet-this-week'>US, Japan leaders ink rare earths deal ahead of Trump-Xi meet this week</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-28/trump-japan-takaichi-trade-rare-earths-defense-meeting/105942246'>Rare earths, golf clubs and utes feature in Japan &#x27;charm offensive&#x27; on Trump</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/week-asia/politics/article/3330597/japans-pm-criticised-curry-favour-trump-over-n